# New Page Creation Checklist

When asked to create any new page, follow these steps in order without skipping.

---

## Step 1 — Identify Shared Components to Import (Do This Before Writing Code)

Check each item. If the answer is yes, import the component — never recreate it.

- Does this page have any section with a label + title + subtitle? → Import `SectionHeader` from `@/components/ui/SectionHeader`
- Does this page have a contact form? → Import `GetInTouchForm` from `@/components/ui/GetInTouchForm`
- Does this page have a FAQ section? → Import `FAQAccordion` from `@/components/ui/FAQAccordion`
- Does this page show product cards? → Import `ProductCard` from `@/components/ui/ProductCard`
- Does this page show service cards? → Import `ServiceCard` from `@/components/ui/ServiceCard`
- Is this a detail or sub-page? → Import `BackButton` from `@/components/ui/BackButton`
- Does this page have a row of stats/numbers? → Import `StatsBar` from `@/components/ui/StatsBar`

---

## Step 2 — Decide File Placement

Run the folder structure decision tree:
```
Is this component used on 2+ unrelated pages?
  YES → src/components/ui/
  NO  → src/pages/[PageName]/components/
```

---

## Step 3 — Create the Folder Structure

```
src/pages/[PageName]/
├── [PageName].jsx        ← main page component
├── index.js              ← re-export only
└── components/           ← page-specific sections only
    └── [SectionName].jsx
```

---

## Step 4 — Write index.js First

```js
// src/pages/[PageName]/index.js
export { default } from './[PageName]';
```

---

## Step 5 — Write the Page Shell

```jsx
// src/pages/[PageName]/[PageName].jsx
import MainLayout from '@/layouts/MainLayout';
import GetInTouchForm from '@/components/ui/GetInTouchForm';
// ... other shared component imports
// ... page-specific section imports

export default function [PageName]() {
  return (
    <MainLayout>
      {/* sections listed top to bottom, matching the visual design */}
      <GetInTouchForm />
    </MainLayout>
  );
}
```

---

## Step 6 — Write Page-Specific Section Components

For each section that does not match any shared component:
- File goes in `src/pages/[PageName]/components/[SectionName].jsx`
- Use a named export: `export function SectionName() {}`
- Import all data from `src/data/` — never define arrays inside the component

---

## Step 7 — Register the Route

1. Add a constant to `src/config/routes.js`:
   ```js
   NEW_PAGE: '/new-page-path',
   ```
2. Add a lazy import and `<Route>` to `src/router.jsx`:
   ```jsx
   const NewPage = lazy(() => import('@/pages/NewPage'));
   <Route path={ROUTES.NEW_PAGE} element={<NewPage />} />
   ```

---

## Step 8 — Final Sanity Check

Before submitting any code, verify every item:

- [ ] No `<Navbar>` or `<Footer>` rendered inside the page
- [ ] No contact form markup rebuilt from scratch
- [ ] No section header rebuilt inline
- [ ] No data arrays defined inside any `.jsx` file
- [ ] All `<Link to="">` and `navigate()` calls use `ROUTES` constants
- [ ] All cross-folder imports use the `@/` alias
- [ ] All shared/UI components use named exports
- [ ] The page default export is wrapped in `<MainLayout>`
- [ ] `index.js` exists in the page folder
- [ ] Route is registered in both `routes.js` and `router.jsx`
